summary:
Five years of Offshore experience on small vessels in the North Sea, Baltic and Irish Sea. Broad experience on geophysical and UXO surveys to provide shallow geophysical insight to wind farm and offshore communications industries.

Competent processing and interpreting Innomar data, gradiometer and side scan sonar datasets using: IHS Kingdom, Petrel, RadEx Pro, Oasis Montaj , SonarWiz, GIS and OpendTect.

Coordinator of deliverables and reports offshore, with a keen focus on collaboration between vessel team and client. Have worked in a supervisory role in China, overseeing a small team of geophysicists in the timely production of deliverables for European offshore wind farm projects.

Up to date BOSIET and offshore medical certification. MMO/PAM observer. 

Two years’ working as a Geophysical Consultant for Terravision Exploration using Ground Penetration Radar to locate; voids, water, minerals, structures etc. in Europe, Asia, Africa, North America and South America.  Experience in the Business development of a small startup company. Responsibilities included; people management, proposal assessment, data collection, report writing and data presentation.
